reviews.text: I've lived in Iowa my whole life and never heard of this cave.I'd say this is a must see if vacationing in the Dubuque/Galena area.  Very fun guide lead a group of 10 of us on an hour tour.if you arrange in advance you can have a tour deeper into the cave. Excellent attraction!

This is an awesome experience!! The tour guide was awesome, patient and answered every question thrown her way.  This was a spur of the moment thing we decided to do when we were in town for a weekend getaway with a couple friend of ours. We all thoroughly enjoyed it.

It was a blast! For $15 you get to experience the caves in the natural state! My 9 year old niece and 6 year old niece enjoyed it a lot! They are in girl scouts and wanted to get their cave badges. Make sure you take a light jacket with cause it's only 52 degrees down in the caves year round! Our guide was AWESOME! She was knowledgeable!
Great stop on a hot day. Been in caves before.  This one was more personal of a tour. It was fun. Not too long. Enjoy exploring.
I really enjoyed it! As did all kids I was with. Make sure you bring a sweater and shoes that can get a little wet. Guide was quirky and fun, and gift shop was neat and well put together.
Wonderful museum. This community puts alot of effort into cultivating their art scene. Dubuque was top notch and the volunteers at the museum were friendly.
Nice... Small but nice.
....a really nice space and with an inspiring permanent collection. Grant Wood's pieces were very informative.
It was interesting exept it under construction only a small portion of the museum was open to the public
Fantastic, progressive Art Museum right in the middle of downtown Dubuque!  Wonderful programs like "Dead Artist Series".  Last program featured amazing local actor nearly channeling "Mark Twain"!

Such an awesome piece of movie history! Watched and loved this movie since I was a little kid. So surreal being there in person. Was able to tour the farm house and play on the field! We made a 100 mile detour just to stop by and is definitely worth it. Especially if you have kids. Play catch and run the bases a must!

I remember coming here a few years ago during the huge dispute between some corporation that owned one side of the field and a family that owned the other...they had some signs that I thought were pretty distasteful as to the dispute between the sides. 

We were there again last week and they must have either reconciled or one of 'em sold out to the other because the signs were gone. They sell ice cream and pop and souvenirs, and you can take your picture in front of the house (bring your own camera). You can walk out onto the field and play, too!

I will never forget this place. Just being there was amazing, but on top of that, I got engaged there! If you love the Field of Dreams movie, this place is a must for your bucket list! Also, take the tour of the house. The tour guide Craig is very knowledgeable and it was a great experience.

This is a really cool place! One of my favorite movies growing up and finally being able to come to this place was awesome! Running the bases and being able to were certain scenes of the movie were filmed was really great! Definitely would like to come back again sometime!

My wife cried she loved it so much...spent hours here... The tour is worth it and the place was well kept. Nearly everything you want to experience is free. Worth the time to visit, if you love baseball and/or the movie.

Firstly, I love the performances here, they're always great fun. It's a great evening out, situated by a train/bus station and surrounded by cheery pubs.
The inside of the building is beautiful, with a wonderfully painted ceiling.

There are three floors, as far as public access goes. There is a lift, but I'm not sure just how accessible seating arrangements are in the building.

I have found the seats to be quite uncomfortable and the safety to be slightly concerning. In the Gods, for example, a small metal bar seems to be the only thing keeping you from plummeting down to the tier below. The seats are uncomfortably close to one another, making viewing slightly unpleasant.

Air conditioning and heating in the building, without a joke, blows hot and cold. I often feel far too warm just as the show begins, then freezing cold midway. 

Despite these issues, I honestly love visiting this place, the shows are always really good, acoustics are great, and service is usually friendly.

I had a wonderful experience at the Grand Opera House. It was like going back in time as the theatre itself seems like it hadn't changed for hundreds of years. Having said that everything was clean and well maintained. I feel like I was bitten by the bug of live theatre and I will definitely be back. Pro tip come early to soak up the atmosphere, the drinks seemed cheaper than the near by pubs too.

The performance was very fast moving & the cast were in top form. Very funny & some hilarious moments.
Audience were very relaxed & appeared to enjoy every moment along with the music.
Enjoyable evening.

Watched give my head peace, great show. Lovely building and the staff were very friendly and professional. Seats we had were a bit cramped for those with legs and feet and over 5' tall. Great experience though I'll be back again.

Beautiful venue, with good views from all areas. Staff are always helpful and we'll informed.It is small so you can't expect to see shows with a massive stage setup there. If you ever have a chance to do their backstage tour during the summer I'd really recommend it

Very nice to visit and learn about some of Dubuque's history. Went there for the Independece Day Ice Cream Social. Musicians, food available for purchase, different stations of interest and activities good for the younger attendees. Overall a nice family outing.
If you deem this review helpful, please give it a like. Thank you.
We went here because my daughter says it is a haunted house. It has great history and is original inside. You can't take pictures in the house but you can outside the house. We loved it.
It was closed the afternoon we went, even though the recording said it would be open. Lovely little exterior too bad we couldn't see the interior.

I have been wanting to go to the 4th of July Ice Cream Social since moving to Dubuque 5 years ago.  They did a great job.  Both of my kids (15 & 4) found different things they each liked between the tours, showing how things were done in the 1800's-early 1900's
Interesting glimpse into local history. appreciate all the volunteers who make the house function. On the 4th they have special tours and Exhibits including actual Cannon being fired
Awesome and don't miss the wood guy's display. Bernie's creations will make your jaw drop and if he's there you'll love his attention to detail and you!

Such a neat place to visit! I actually came to take some pictures and get info about upcoming exhibits. Not being a farm kid myself, I wasn't overly excited about the visit. However, the museum manager, Amanda Schwartz, was incredibly helpful and informative. I came by myself on an afternoon and she took the time out of her day to walk me through the museum and explain each of the new exhibits. I can tell that Schwartz really enjoys what she does. After the guided tour, she let me explore by myself for a while. Might I just say, the remote control tractors are for kids at heart too! A lot of fun to be had and knowledge to be gained at the museum. Recommended for people of all ages because of interactive exhibits.
Great place for family fun. Nat'l toy show usually yields any toy you are looking for or person who knows someone who does have what you need. Happy hunting!!
Very informative,  lots of toy tractors from around the world. Very clean and organized.
This is the second visit for my 87 year old father. He loves it! Brings about great memories for him!
They had wines for both sweet and dry tastes. The staff was friendly and the cheesy bread was great to snack on. I will definitely return to this winery again!
The views of the valley , the wine , and the pizza are all great! The pizza isn’t like other wood fire pizza where it’s crusty and burnt. I would save every carb just to indulge in this pizza ♥️
Beautiful inside and out! Very pleasant gal that helped us. Great  experience !
Great, knowledgeable staff.  After a wine tasting grab a bottle of wine and a stone oven pizza, delicious.  Thanks to Park Farm Winery for the excellent time.  We enjoyed the Willow, dry white.

Very nice winery set in a beautiful location just outside of Doubouqe. Really enjoyed the drive and scenery on the drive there. Huge outdoor and indoor seating areas. Really enjoyed our pizza and wine tasting. Loved their sweet reds and fruit wines.

Would suggest a larger tasting area. I felt rushed and the staff looked overwhelmed. People who were already seated came to the tasting area for beverages and it gets really crowded. Otherwise a great spot!
Food was very good. Service fast and friendly.  Liked the different choices.  Not you same old food. We will go back.

Wait staff was very friendly. When asked what to recommend, she had many ideas. The fried ice cream is everything they say it is... it is very awesome and big! Big enough to share. Only one complaint,  the bathrooms... need another toilet there...
Good homemade pizza. They have lots of other choices on the menu. The restaurant was clean and the service was good. Nice location in historic downtown.
The food was great. And everyone working were great because they were so busy due to concert at Five Flags. Great!!

Third time going here the first time ordered a pork tenderloin it was so hard I couldn't even bite into it nor RIP into it.
Second time pizza nice!!
Ordered out one two of there samples
I opened in store to check for ranch and decided to try a cheese ball soggy. I asked the guy if they were just made?
he asked a couple men then said yes 
I showed him how they look and nothing was done. Took my food and 
That will most definitely be my last time visiting this place.

Do you ever have a destination restaurant? We met up with family here just because of the atmosphere and the great food + the great price! Love the Easter decorations and took several photos. We got some great ideas for our own decorations! We also did a little wine tasting next door of the local vintners, yes we did buy some! We have to do this more often!

Service and staff were fantastic. Food was okay, but not amazing. The quality of the buffet options could have been better. If you enjoy a relaxed visit to a historic spot in Iowa, while taking care of your hunger, this is the spot!

The food is so great here and their staff is phenomenal. We had a reservation, but ended up having a few members of our party flake out and they still managed to get us seated pretty quickly. Best Lent buffet around!

So welcoming that you often feel like family. My favorite two meals here are the prime rib and the catfish. Their fries are honestly the best I have ever had. The fries are not overly crispy where they're hard, not soggy, but just the perfect crunch. You cannot go wrong with any of the pies, but I love the raspberry!

This place and the Breitbach family have really kept things kicking after 2 building fires in the past. I have eaten for as long as I can remember with my family, and it's always a pleasure. The involvement of family is awesome.

Valentine's Day buffet. Arrived at 6pm at peak dining time and was seated within 5 minutes. Prime rib buffet tasted very good along with the fried fish. Drove over an hour to try this place. I would definitely go again if I was in the area.
